This paper deals with mechanism design in a two-sided market with private values, which is a classic topic in game theory and economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves designing incentive-compatible mechanisms, which is a central problem in mechanism design and falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions Bayesian settings and prior distributions, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
